<statement>
<p>28 is what percent of 20? <input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/><percent/> </p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>140</li></ul></p><p>Because we are asked for 28 of 20 we calculate,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\frac{{28}}{{20}}={1.4}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{1.4}\times{100}={140}</m>.</p>
<p>The result is greater than 100<percent/>, because the new amount is greater than the original amount.</p>
</solution>
